**Legislation**: Senators introduce, vote on, and shape laws that affect the entire country.
They work with fellow lawmakers to draft, at propose legislation addressing various issues.
They work with representatives from the House of Representatives to pass bills, which are then sent to the President for signing or veto.
They work with fellow lawmakers to create, and refine bills that address various national issues.
They work with other lawmakers to draft, debate, and refine bills that ultimately become federal statutes.
They sponsor or co-sponsor bills, the legislative process begins.
